Come on, guys! 
Over here, now!

5
00:00:17,935 --> 00:00:19,241
Listen up, listen up.

6
00:00:19,241 --> 00:00:21,067
We're down one and we need a score.

7
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:23,789
You boys do what I tell you, 
you'll be state champinos!

8
00:00:23,789 --> 00:00:25,653
I want the ball in Herman's hand.

9
00:00:25,653 --> 00:00:28,724
The rest of you guys just clear 
out of his way, you understand?

10
00:00:28,724 --> 00:00:30,439
All right, bring it in. 
Saints on three.

11
00:00:30,439 --> 00:00:32,933
- One, two, three... 
- Saints!

12
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:34,585
Herman...

13
00:00:35,556 --> 00:00:38,484
Put us your back and get us a win.

14
00:00:38,950 --> 00:00:40,615
Let's go, Herman, baby!

15
00:00:40,615 --> 00:00:42,212
Herman, Herman, 
do your uncle right, baby.

16
00:00:42,212 --> 00:00:43,306
Do your uncle right!

17
00:00:43,306 --> 00:00:46,443
Please, Lord, give young Herman 
the strength to do me right.

18
00:00:46,443 --> 00:00:48,669
Please! Come on, Herman. 
Come on, baby.

19
00:00:48,669 --> 00:00:51,489
Let's do it, baby. 
Come on.

20
00:02:24,073 --> 00:02:26,813
You figure 6:00 a.m.'s the right 
time to start the day, boss?

21
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:29,239
These guys have been 
here for an hour, Lil.

22
00:02:29,722 --> 00:02:32,198
You ever hear of Herman Lester?

23
00:02:32,198 --> 00:02:33,372
No.

24
00:02:33,372 --> 00:02:35,807
Ah, he's only the best basketball 
player who ever lived.

25
00:02:35,807 --> 00:02:37,855
Yeah? / And died.

26
00:02:37,855 --> 00:02:42,206
He was murdered on a playground 
court in 1987. Never sloved.

27
00:02:42,559 --> 00:02:44,844
So what are we doing here?

28
00:02:44,844 --> 00:02:46,863
You see the kid with the ball?

29
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:51,937
That's Herman's son.

30
00:02:58,425 --> 00:03:00,379
Ball never touches the floor.

31
00:03:01,619 --> 00:03:04,206
And make the layup now.
Let's go!

32
00:03:04,206 --> 00:03:06,053
John. / Coach.

33
00:03:06,053 --> 00:03:07,810
- Thanks for coming.
- No problem.

34
00:03:07,810 --> 00:03:09,675
This is Detective Rush.

35
00:03:09,675 --> 00:03:11,681
- Nice to meet you.
- Pleasure.

36
00:03:11,681 --> 00:03:13,824
Look, look, watch this.

37
00:03:15,601 --> 00:03:18,885
Doesn't have Herman's 
size, but ... more range.

38
00:03:18,885 --> 00:03:20,095
And the same confidence.

39
00:03:20,095 --> 00:03:23,445
I tell you, John, it's like 
coaching Herman all over again.

40
00:03:23,445 --> 00:03:25,032
Hey, Ray! Come here!

41
00:03:25,032 --> 00:03:27,429
Let's have him walk us
through this phone call he got.

42
00:03:27,429 --> 00:03:29,152
Some kind of threat?

43
00:03:29,152 --> 00:03:30,898
Ray, these are Philadelphia police.

44
00:03:30,898 --> 00:03:31,668
Gonna help us out.

45
00:03:31,668 --> 00:03:33,908
Hey. / Hey.

46
00:03:33,908 --> 00:03:35,992
Hi, Ray.

47
00:03:35,992 --> 00:03:38,103
Want to tell us about 
the phone call you got?

48
00:03:38,103 --> 00:03:39,292
Not much to it.

49
00:03:39,292 --> 00:03:41,460
I'm home, pick up the phone and hear.

50
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:42,699
If I play Friday night,

51
00:03:42,699 --> 00:03:45,267
I'm gonna get the screwdriver, 
just like my dad.

52
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:46,515
Screwdriver?

53
00:03:46,515 --> 00:03:49,032
It was the murder weapon.

54
00:03:50,025 --> 00:03:53,794
So... what's Friday night?

55
00:03:54,829 --> 00:03:56,941
State championship.

56
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:02,683
Uh, no idea who it was 
male, female, young, old?

57
00:04:02,683 --> 00:04:05,595
Male. Can't say about the rest.

58
00:04:05,595 --> 00:04:08,026
Ray, you having any problem in school?

59
00:04:08,026 --> 00:04:10,106
Any issues on or off the court?

60
00:04:10,106 --> 00:04:12,164
Nah. Things are cool.

61
00:04:12,164 --> 00:04:14,077
Okay, Ray. Thanks.

62
00:04:14,077 --> 00:04:15,837
Back out there.

63
00:04:16,911 --> 00:04:19,547
I need him in the lineup Friday.

64
00:04:20,396 --> 00:04:24,036
Do really think this threat is 
connected to Herman's murder?

65
00:04:24,831 --> 00:04:26,716
Well, the kid's a phenom like his dad.

66
00:04:26,716 --> 00:04:29,798
They both lead their teams 
to the state championship.

67
00:04:29,798 --> 00:04:31,302
Herman gets murdered,

68
00:04:31,302 --> 00:04:32,960
now Ray gets this death threat.

69
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:34,689
Enough connection for me.

70
00:04:34,689 --> 00:04:35,764
We'll check with the phone company,

71
00:04:35,764 --> 00:04:38,547
see if we can trace where 
the call came from.

72
00:04:40,043 --> 00:04:42,385
And pull Herman Lester's case.

